command: from worldsim.rules import default_ruleset; from worldsim.types import Position, Agent, SimConfig; import random; agents = {Position(r,c): Agent(10,0,r%4) for r in range(4) for c in range(4) if (r+c)%3!=0}; cfg = SimConfig(width=5, height=5, seed=42); new_a, b, d, m = default_ruleset(agents, 5, 5, cfg, random.Random(42)); assert len(agents)+b-d == len(new_a), f'pop invariant: {len(agents)}+{b}-{d}!={len(new_a)}'

from worldsim.rules import default_ruleset; from worldsim.types import Position, Agent, SimConfig; import random; agents = {Position(r,c): Agent(10,0,r%4) for r in range(4) for c in range(4) if (r+c)%3!=0}; cfg = SimConfig(width=5, height=5, seed=42); new_a, b, d, m = default_ruleset(agents, 5, 5, cfg, random.Random(42)); positions = list(new_a.keys()); assert len(positions) == len(set(positions)), 'duplicate positions'

from worldsim.rules import default_ruleset; from worldsim.types import Position, Agent, SimConfig; import random; agents = {Position(0,0): Agent(10,0,0), Position(1,1): Agent(10,0,2)}; cfg = SimConfig(width=5, height=5, seed=42); r1 = default_ruleset(dict(agents), 5, 5, cfg, random.Random(42)); r2 = default_ruleset(dict(agents), 5, 5, cfg, random.Random(42)); assert r1 == r2, 'not deterministic'
